text: @curiouswavefn We at @Citrine_io actually use AI in chemistry to help with design of experiment. The goal is that the scientist can focus on higher level strategic decisions and validation. Has had a huge impact already. Would love to connect and hear more of your thoughts!

text: For instance, I think medicinal chemists need to spend much more time on biology and design of experiments. One way to do this: imagine that an AI makes you on-demand molecules - what problem would that enable you to solve? Think about that higher level function.

text: To put it another way: If synthesis planning AI makes enough of an impact so that chemists can spend 20% more time deciding *what* to make and what problem to solve instead of *how* to make something, that's a pretty important contribution.
